Forty-fifth Avenue (foreground, to be constructed) at the S.E. corner of 90th Street (right, partially seen). At tue right background is seen the 3 story Newtown High School on the east side of 90th Street (Chicago Street) between Forty-eight and Fiftieth Avenues. At the left foreground ,rear view.is seen, facing on Newtown Avenue, from right to left St. Mark's African Methodist Episcopal Church, the rectory, and a group of two etory homes in the former cemet'ry grounds surrounding the Church. Also shown are buildings on the south side of Newtown Avenue, east of 90th Street. Anothcr steeple seen in the center background is that of
P.S. No. 13.
